Mature specimens purplish. This colour is observed predominantly on dorsal, anal, adipose, caudal and pelvic fins, extending also over ventral area (
Figure 9
). Lateral line with golden shades predominantly between pelvic and anal fins. Head, with golden line behind eye, followed by a black line and golden point at end of opercle, as well as a black humeral blotch. First portion of dorsal fin (first two rays) golden in colour. Head with a band that is smaller than pupil, extending from front edge of eye to beginning of maxillary bone.
